lenders.name: RHonda
lenders.whereabouts: Bocas del Toro Bocas del Toro
lenders.loan_because: I am an entrepreneur that has been traveling around the world for 6 years, and we want to give back to other global entrepreneurs.  Kiva makes it easy for us to give because everything is internet based.
lenders.occupational_info:
We are the Unstoppable Family.....Brian, Rhonda and our daughter, Hanalei Swan (now 6 years old).

We have been traveling the world for over 5 years...inspiring people to live our their dreams by using Personal Development and Free Enterprise.

Our mission is to enjoy Life to the fullest and to be the example to individuals, couples and families that you can Live &Travel wherever you want in this world while thriving financially, mentally, physically & spiritually. 

We have been put on this planet to show that you do not have to work your Butt off for years and save money to travel, then live on a budget until your money runs out...only to return back to the JOB you hated in the 1st place.

My wife, Rhonda Swan, & I are polar opposites. I am a relaxed go-with-the flow, hippy surfer guy and for Rhonda her idea of relaxing is running around in circles; she’s someone that makes coffee nervous. But as a family, we're Unstoppable.

We have been traveling around the world for past 4.5 Years with our 6 year old daughter Hanalei, who can throw a few Bahasa Indonesian words into her sentences and thinks it is quite normal to get from A to B on a motorbike with her mother wearing her little baby pink custom helmet. A monkey next to the swimming pool? Oh that’s just a normal occurrence.

From Hawaii, Mexico, Costa Rica, Nicaragua, Bali, Fiji, Australia, Panama, Peru, Brazil & snowboarding in Lake Tahoe for a season… we are literally seeking an Endless Journey!

We used to work in the corporate world wearing suits and earning six figure salaries back in San Diego. Rhonda was a sales executive for a large pharmaceutical company and I was an engineer- we were driving a Mercedes and an Escalade and buying and selling million dollar homes. We had the house, the car and the lifestyle that most people dream of and aspire to.

But 8.5 years ago Rhonda assessed her life and decided that she couldn’t face putting her child through daycare. We quit our jobs and started a portable business working in personal development for a lifestyle company, teaching people how to create wealth and live the lifestyle of their dreams.

Things haven’t been all roses Us. As we began to buy and sell more properties we invested money in a golf course and property development, but the money disappeared and the golf course was never built, resulting in an expensive court battle. We lost all of our money, sold our homes and we decided that we could either stay and rebuild our lives in San Diego, or pursue our dream to travel the world and we let go of our material things.

We departed San Diego on Nov 25th, 2008 and started our journey in Hanalei Bay, Kauai. We then celebrated our 5 year wedding anniversary 3 days later in the same spot we were married and also named our now 5 year old daughter after, Hanalei Swan. 

After 4.5 Years of travel...we are having as much fun as when we started! 

You can also join us on our journey here as well... 
http://unstoppablefamily.com/
https://www.facebook.com/unstoppablefamily
http://twitter.com/#!/unstoppablefam

Cheers from the Unstoppable Family...back in the USA!
Brian, Rhonda & Hanalei Swan
